# C# Conventions

- Target framework: .NET 8
- Use file-scoped namespaces only when consistent with existing code (this project uses block-scoped)
- Use `record` for Commands and Queries
- Use `sealed` on exception classes and handlers where appropriate
- Throw domain exceptions (`NotFoundException`, `BadRequestException`) — never return error codes
- Use `ArgumentNullException.ThrowIfNull()` for guard clauses
- Avoid comments that just narrate what the code does
